import React from "react";
import { Typography, Box, Button } from "@mui/material";

const HomePage = () => {
    return ( 
        <Box>
            {/* Navbar goes here */}
            <Box sx={{
                border:1,
                borderColor: 'grey.500',
                width: '60%',
                margin: 'auto',
                padding: '2rem'
            }}>
                <Typography 
                variant="h4"
                align="center"
                gutterBottom>
                    Welcome to Tinder Paws!
                </Typography>
                <Typography 
                variant="body1"
                align="center"
                gutterBottom>
                    We are as excited as you to being your companion finding journey! 
                </Typography>

                <Typography 
                align="center"
                gutterBottom>
                    Here you will able to look through all animals at different shelters and match with the ones you like. 
                </Typography>

                <Typography 
                align="center"
                gutterBottom>
                    Our team will then contact you to start an application process and for you to meet your match. 
                </Typography>

                <Typography
                align="center"
                gutterBottom>
                    After the screening, you will be able to take your companion home!
                </Typography>

                <Typography
                align="center">
                    Here are the steps:
                </Typography>
            </Box>
            <Button variant="contained" href="/signUp" margin="auto">
                Get Started!
            </Button>
        </Box>
     );
}
 
export default HomePage;
